sources.description: Impact is a 1949 American film noir drama film starring Brian Donlevy and Ella Raines . Directed by Arthur Lubin , it was shot entirely in Northern California , including scenes in Sausalito at Larkspur in Marin County , on Nob Hill in San Francisco , and throughout the Bay area. The screenplay was based on a story by film noir writer Jay Dratler . Charles Coburn , Helen Walker , Anna May Wong , Philip Ahn , and William Wright appear in support. Lubin called it "a very, very good picture" with "a very nice cast."
